<subSubSection id="1EF421CCFFD0C171FF37D926FBC57B81" lastPageId="75" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="56517247FFD0C171FF37D926FBC57B81" blockId="74.[151,1437,1339,2013]" lastBlockId="75.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="75" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FFD0C170FF37D926FECD7CC1" bold="true" box="[199,315,1915,1941]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Remarks.</emphasis>
Collection locality notes (R. Rakitov, pers. comm.) recorded the habitat as a dry meadow among pine-yucca forest, with 
<taxonomicName id="91EE09C4FFD0C170FE6ED9C2FE0C7CED" box="[414,506,1951,1977]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Opuntia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FFD0C170FE6ED9C2FE0C7CED" box="[414,506,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Opuntia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and many dry forbs. It would be preferable to describe this species with at least one male specimen, but 
<taxonomicName id="91EE09C4FFD0C170FE8AD99EFDE57C88" authorityName="Zahniser" authorityYear="2021" box="[378,531,1987,2012]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hecullus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis id="649AAE55FFD0C170FE8AD99EFDE57C88" box="[378,531,1987,2012]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">H. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly different and easily separated from the other two species in the genus based on the female. Its discovery substantially expands the known geographic range of the genus. Future collecting efforts directed near the 
<typeStatus id="8955CCE5FFD1C171FE58DEE6FE2E7B81" box="[424,472,187,213]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">type</typeStatus>
locality may reveal more specimens including males.
</paragraph>
